content:
You can call Data Mappers using Apex or a REST API. You can also use custom input and output and environment variables in Data Mappers.

Omnistudio Data Mapper REST API
You can invoke any type of Data Mapper using the Data Mapper REST API. To update Salesforce objects, issue a POST request with a JSON payload. To retrieve data from Salesforce, issue a GET call to a Data Mapper Extract.

To call a Data Mapper from Apex, call the vlocity_ins.DRGlobal.processObjectsJSON() method. The DRGlobal class provides multiple methods for calling Omnistudio Data Mappers from Apex.
Environment Variables can be used in Formulas and Default Values. Custom Input and Output can be configured to handle other data formats.
